&lt;p&gt;Python&amp;rsquo;s default package manager, &lt;code&gt;pip&lt;/code&gt;, is excellent for installing packages. However, when it comes to managing project-specific dependencies and virtual environments, &lt;code&gt;pip&lt;/code&gt; alone can feel a bit basic. Developers often find themselves juggling &lt;code&gt;pip&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;virtualenv&lt;/code&gt; (or Python&amp;rsquo;s built-in &lt;code&gt;venv&lt;/code&gt; module), manually creating environments, activating them via specific scripts, and managing &lt;code&gt;requirements.txt&lt;/code&gt; files.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>